  [38;2;177;185;249madd_score()[39m tries to write to [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[s->num_scores][39m, it attempts to
  dereference a NULL pointer, causing the crash.

  [1mDETAILED ANALYSIS[22m:
  1. In [38;2;177;185;249mcreate_student()[39m (lines 12-22), memory is allocated for the Student
   structure itself
  2. The [38;2;177;185;249mname[39m field is properly allocated and initialized
  3. However, line 18 shows the proper allocation is commented out: [38;2;177;185;249m// [39m
  s->scores = malloc(100 * sizeof(float));
  4. Line 19 explicitly sets [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores = NULL[39m
  5. When [38;2;177;185;249mmain()[39m calls [38;2;177;185;249madd_score(alice, 95.5)[39m (line 56), the function tries
   to write to [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[0][39m
  6. Since [38;2;177;185;249ms->scores[39m is NULL, this becomes a write to address 0x0,
  triggering the segmentation fault
